Opinion writers and editorial boards are praising President Trump's first State of the Union Address. They describe it as a well-crafted and well-delivered speech that highlighted the economy, accomplishments, and the importance of security. The speech was seen as moving, reasonable, and bipartisan. A CBS News-YouGov instant poll found that 75 percent of viewers approved of Trump's speech. It was also noted that Trump called for unity and celebrated America's innovative and entrepreneurial spirit. The speech addressed the issue of international terrorism and emphasized the importance of countering terrorist groups. Overall, the speech was seen as uplifting, strong, and a reminder of why people voted for Trump. It touched on various topics, including infrastructure, tax cuts, Wall Street, and the fight against ISIS.